# ── GoalCert Scenario Engine — configuration ──────────────────────────
# Copy to backend/.env and fill in. .env is gitignored, so THIS FILE is the only
# spec a teammate cloning the repo gets. Keep it current.
#
# For AWS, see AWS_DEPLOYMENT.md (§5.1).

# ── LLM ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠ REQUIRED for AI scenario AUTHORING (/scenarios/author) and REVISION
#   (/scenarios/{id}/revise — the Builder's "Customise with AI").
#
# This engine calls Claude DIRECTLY for both. (An older note here claimed the key
# was "optional, legacy /studio + /jilla only" and that authoring was delegated to
# the Agentic AI platform — that is no longer true. Delegation is only the FALLBACK
# used when this key is absent.)
#
# Without it those two endpoints return a clear 422 and everything else works:
# the library, cascade runs, simulation, Monte Carlo and reports never use an LLM.
# The model writes the scenario SPEC; engine/graph.py still computes what happens.
#
# Also make sure the SDK is installed — `pip install -r requirements.txt`. It is in
# requirements.txt but a venv created before it was added will 500 with an empty body.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
AUTHORING_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# ── Auth ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shared secret. When set, EVERY request except GET /health must carry it in
# X-API-Key — set the SAME value in the hub's SCENARIO_API_KEY.
#
# ⚠ UNSET MEANS ALLOW-ALL. Fine locally. In a deploy it means this engine's
# multi-tenancy is decoration: scoping trusts the X-Goalcert-Org header, which is
# only trustworthy because the hub's gateway is the sole ingress AND this key is
# set. Anything that can reach the engine directly can pick its own tenant.
SCENARIO_API_KEY=

# ── Persistence ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default is a local SQLite file. Fine for dev, WRONG for any deploy: on Fargate
# the file dies with the task and every AUTHORED scenario goes with it. The seeded
# scenarios survive (they self-register from scenarios/definitions/** on boot) —
# the ones your users wrote do not.
# Verified working on Postgres; the org_id migration runs automatically on boot.
# GOALCERT_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@db-host:5432/scenario
# GOALCERT_DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./simulation_engine.db

# ── CORS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JSON list. Only needed when a BROWSER fetches from this engine — i.e. when this
# service also serves the federated remote (the local setup: frontend/dist at "/").
# Defaults to empty, which BLOCKS the hub from loading remoteEntry.js cross-origin.
# On AWS the remote is served by CloudFront, so this can stay empty.
# "*" is rejected by browsers alongside credentialed requests — list origins explicitly.
# GOALCERT_CORS_ORIGINS=["http://127.0.0.1:8090","http://localhost:8090"]

# ── Other platforms (server-to-server) ────────────────────────────────
#  * Agentic AI — the FALLBACK authoring path used only when ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#    above is blank (services/agent_client.py).
#    Local port is 8097 (docker-compose maps 8097:8000); the container listens on
#    8000. An older default of 8001 here was wrong and produced 503s.
#  * Digital Twin — reserved for twin-grounded scenarios (services/twin_client.py).
AGENTIC_AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8097
DIGITAL_TWIN_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
